  "texts": [
    "Such data can provide valuable insights into the subjective nature of a patient's medical condition, Page 49 of 72 80 including their symptoms, emotions, and experiences, which may not be accurately captured by numerical or categorical data alone.",
    "Additionally, textual data can be leveraged to identify patterns and relationships between medical conditions and patient characteristics, paving the way for developing personalised treatment plans.",
    "Assessing the performance of cost-sensitive algorithms in medical applications requires appropriate performance metrics.",
    "Two categories of metrics commonly used in the literature are traditional metrics and cost-related metrics.",
    "This study focuses on presenting the commonly used metrics from both categories."
  ]
}